# Infrastructure Layer

Driven adapters. Implements outbound ports defined in `application/ports/outbound/`.

## Subpackages

| Path | Implements | Technology (_ADR_) |
|------|------------|-------------------|
| `database/` | Repository ports | SQLAlchemy — models stay here, not in domain |
| `ai/yolo/` | `PlateDetectionPort` | YOLO |
| `ocr/paddleocr/` | `OcrPort` | PaddleOCR |
| `pdf/` | `PdfGeneratorPort` | PDF library TBD |
| `authentication/` | Auth providers | JWT |
| `logging/` | `LoggingPort` | Structured logging |
| `external/vehicle_registry/` | `VehicleRegistryPort` | HTTP client |
| `config/loaders/` | `ConfigurationPort` | YAML + env |

## Rules

- Implement **one port per adapter class** (or cohesive port group).
- Map ORM models ↔ domain entities in `database/mappers/` — never expose ORM to application.
- OpenCV usage allowed **only** in `infrastructure/` (e.g. OCR preprocessor) — never `domain/`.
- Catch vendor exceptions; wrap in `InfrastructureError` with safe messages.

## SQL

- All SQL/ORM queries live in `infrastructure/database/repositories/`.
- Repositories implement port interfaces — no query logic in use cases or handlers.

## ML Pipelines

- `infrastructure/ai/pipelines/` wires detector + recognizer for Vehicle Scan module.
- Return DTOs matching `docs/ai-pipeline/pipeline-interfaces.md` contracts.
- Include `model_version` on every inference result.

## Must NOT

- Import from `interfaces/` (handlers).
- Contain business rules (risk thresholds → `domain/risk/`).
